Subject: Re: [FairfieldLife] Re: The Dalai Lama and the Science of Meditation

Dear Tobin,

Thank you for your response. I understand your perspective and respect your beliefs. I also appreciate your willingness to engage in a respectful dialogue.

I would like to clarify that I am not advocating for a particular religious or spiritual belief system. Rather, I am simply suggesting that there may be more to our existence than what we can perceive with our senses and that exploring these possibilities through meditation and other contemplative practices may be beneficial for our well-being.

I also want to emphasize that science and spirituality are not mutually exclusive. In fact, many scientists and philosophers have recognized the importance of incorporating spiritual and ethical considerations into their work. For example, Albert Einstein famously said, "The most beautiful thing we can experience is the mysterious. It is the source of all true art and all science."

Again, I appreciate your willingness to engage in this dialogue and hope that we can continue to have respectful conversations about these important topics.

Best regards,

Matthew J. Dowd

res:
EBS stands for Elastic Block Store, which is a fully managed, persistent data storage service provided by Amazon Web Services (AWS). EBS provides scalable, high-performance block-level storage for Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) instances, allowing users to store and retrieve data from their instances.

EBS volumes are available in a variety of storage types, including General Purpose (SSD), Cold HDD, and Archive HDD. Users can choose the storage type that best fits their needs based on factors such as performance, cost, and durability.

EBS volumes can be attached to EC2 instances, allowing users to store data locally on their instances. EBS volumes can also be detached from instances and used as standalone data storage, making it easy to move data between instances or between different regions.

EBS is a popular storage option for AWS users due to its scalability, performance, and reliability. It is commonly used for a wide range of applications, including web servers, databases, and big data processing.
